setup:
A developer writes this code to update prices on a product page:

```js
const priceElement = document.querySelector('.price');
priceElement.innerHTML = '$' + userInput;
```

Where `userInput` comes from a form field the user filled in.

A junior developer writes code to display a list of users:

```js
function displayUsers(users) {
  const list = document.querySelector('#user-list');
  users.forEach(user => {
    list.innerHTML += '<li>' + user.name + '</li>';
  });
}
```

The code works, but a senior developer says it has a performance problem.
